    dc:title "Phylogeny and revised classification of the saucer bugs (Hemiptera: Nepomorpha: Naucoridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994615>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994617>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994637>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994645>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994647>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994664>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994641> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994615>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Foretibiae and foretarsi of Laccocorinae: Ctenipocoris asiaticus (a), Heleolaccocoris ovatus (b), Namtokocoris dalanta (c)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994615/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994617>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Heleocoris elongatus mesofemur (a), metafemur (b), Tsingala gen. nov. sp. C mesofemur (c), metafemur (d). White arrows indicate posteroventral spine rows, black arrows indicate anteroventral spine rows." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994617/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994637>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Mesotibia and mesotarsus of male and female Heleolaccocoris ovatus showing a sexually dimorphic ventral tomentose pad of hairs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994637/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994645>
    dc:description "Figure 14. Revised generic representation of the former genus Heleocoris. Dorsal habitus of Heleocoris vicinus (a), Laccocoris minisculus (b), Heleolaccocoris ovatus (c), Tsingala humeralis (d)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994645/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994647>
    dc:description "Figure 15. Revised generic representation of the former genus Laccocoris. Dorsal habitus of Laccocoris spurcus (a), Heleolaccocoris horvathi (b)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994647/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994664>
    dc:description "Figure 21. Heleolaccocoris horvathi male: dorsal habitus (a), genital capsule with terga IX and X removed (b)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6994641>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Detail of Most Probable Phylogeny dendogram of Laccocorinae.The red-coloured clade includes the Madagascar genera Temnocoris and Tsingala gen. nov.(formerly Heleocoris). The blue-coloured clade represents Heleolaccocoris gen.nov., which comprises species of the former genera Heleocoris and Laccocoris. All species of Tsingala gen. nov. and Heleolaccocoris gen. nov. are new combinations. Geographic associations for major clades within and among tribes are indicated. The red box in the inset shows the part of Figure 9 depicted in this figure." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6994641/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

